    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Air-blowing tools of varied design but that share an attached pair of bowl-like chambers with long ducts emerging from the base of each. A diaphragm is fitted over each chamber, and these are manipulated to draw and force air from the bellows.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
